INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'f1f0fd4b-2957-4eef-aaed-b1ce4e3cd516',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$NestJS Global Exception Filters — Consistent Error Responses Across Your Entire API$escape$,
  $escape$NestJS's built-in `HttpException` gives you structured errors, but the default format varies and unhandled exceptions leak stack traces. The fix: a single `@Catch()` global filter that intercepts everything.

Decorate a class with `@Catch()` (no arguments) to catch all exceptions — both `HttpException` subclasses and unexpected `Error` instances. Inside `catch()`, extract the status and message, then return a uniform envelope: `{ statusCode, message, path, timestamp }`. Register it globally in `main.ts` via `app.useGlobalFilters(new AllExceptionsFilter())`.

For DI-aware filters (e.g., injecting a logger), skip `useGlobalFilters` and instead provide the filter in `AppModule` using the `APP_FILTER` token from `@nestjs/core`. This ensures the filter participates in the NestJS DI lifecycle.

Pair this with NestJS's `HttpExceptionFilter` as a base class if you only want to handle HTTP exceptions and let a broader filter handle the rest. Layering filters — most specific first, broadest last — gives you granular control without duplicating logic.$escape$,
  $escape$@Catch()
export class AllExceptionsFilter implements ExceptionFilter {
  catch(exception: unknown, host: ArgumentsHost) {
    const ctx = host.switchToHttp();
    const response = ctx.getResponse<Response>();
    const request = ctx.getRequest<Request>();

    const status =
      exception instanceof HttpException
        ? exception.getStatus()
        : HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;

    const message =
      exception instanceof HttpException
        ? exception.message
        : 'Internal server error';

    response.status(status).json({
      statusCode: status,
      message,
      path: request.url,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
    });
  }
}$escape$,
