INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '10e6125b-0fa8-4e51-b6ca-176198101998',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$NestJS API Versioning — URI, Header, and OpenAPI in One Setup$escape$,
  $escape$NestJS ships first-class versioning via `VersioningType` in `main.ts`. Enable URI versioning with `app.enableVersioning({ type: VersioningType.URI })`, then decorate controllers with `@Controller({ version: '1', path: 'users' })` or override per-route with `@Version('2')`. For header-based versioning, swap to `VersioningType.HEADER` and specify `header: 'X-API-Version'` — no route changes needed. MediaType versioning (`Accept: application/vnd.api+json;version=2`) is also supported.

For OpenAPI, pair `@nestjs/swagger` with `DocumentBuilder`. Call `addServer()` per environment and use `@ApiHeader()` or let the versioning module auto-prefix paths. Tag controllers with `@ApiTags('users')` and decorate DTOs with `@ApiProperty()` — Swagger UI reflects versioned routes automatically. Mark deprecated endpoints with `@ApiOperation({ deprecated: true })` rather than deleting them, giving consumers a migration window. Use `SwaggerModule.createDocument()` with `deepScanRoutes: true` to catch lazily-loaded module routes. Pin the spec at `/api/docs` behind an auth guard in production — never expose it publicly.$escape$,
  $escape$// main.ts
app.enableVersioning({ type: VersioningType.URI });

const config = new DocumentBuilder()
  .setTitle('ByteAI API')
  .setVersion('1.0')
  .addBearerAuth()
  .build();

const document = SwaggerModule.createDocument(app, config, {
  deepScanRoutes: true,
});
SwaggerModule.setup('api/docs', app, document);

// users.controller.ts
@ApiTags('users')
@Controller({ version: '1', path: 'users' })
export class UsersV1Controller {}

@Controller({ version: '2', path: 'users' })
export class UsersV2Controller {}$escape$,
